@startuml
title Attendance Finalization - Main and Alternative Flows
autonumber
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAF7
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #9A8700

actor Profesor as Teacher
participant "React attendance panel" as UI
participant "Express middleware\nsession + RBAC + Zod" as Middleware
participant AttendanceController as Controller
participant AttendanceService as Service
participant AccessPolicy as Policy
participant "DatabaseContext\ntransaction" as Tx
database PostgreSQL as DB
participant AuditService as Audit
participant CacheService as Cache

Teacher -> UI: Open class attendance
UI -> Middleware: GET /api/v1/class-sessions/{id}/roster
Middleware -> Controller: authenticated scoped request
Controller -> Service: getSessionRoster(actor, sessionId)
Service -> Policy: teacherOwnsSession(actor, sessionId)
Policy -> DB: session + group + teacher + enrollments
DB --> Policy: authorized class context
Service -> DB: active enrollment episodes covering session
DB --> Service: roster and existing records
Service --> UI: roster, state and editable flags

Teacher -> UI: Mark present/late/absent and finalize
UI -> Middleware: PUT .../{id}/attendance\nrecords[], finalize=true, expectedState
Middleware -> Middleware: validate session, role and body
Middleware -> Controller: valid command
Controller -> Service: recordSessionAttendance(actor, id, command)
Service -> Policy: verify teacher/director resource scope
Service -> Service: validate unique students and statuses
Service -> Service: require class ended before finalization

alt valid roster and unchanged attendance state
  Service -> Tx: begin transaction
  Tx -> DB: upsert each attendance record\nwith recorder/updater and version
  Tx -> DB: mark class attendanceState=finalized\nand finalizedBy/finalizedAt
  Tx -> Audit: log ATTENDANCE_BATCH_RECORDED\nand ATTENDANCE_FINALIZED
  Audit -> DB: append audit logs
  Tx --> Service: commit
  Service -> Cache: invalidate attendance/reports/students tags
  Service --> Controller: finalized roster result
  Controller --> UI: 200 success
  UI --> Teacher: Confirmation and locked roster
else stale state, invalid student or unauthorized class
  Service --> Controller: AppError 403/409/422
  Controller --> UI: consistent error envelope
  UI --> Teacher: Friendly correction message
end

opt authorized correction after finalization
  Teacher -> UI: Enable correction and enter reason
  UI -> Service: PUT attendance with correctionReason
  Service -> Policy: allow correction role and scope
  Service -> DB: update record, increment version, preserve history fields
  Service -> Audit: log ATTENDANCE_CORRECTED with reason
  Service -> Cache: invalidate affected report tags
  Service --> UI: corrected record
end
@enduml
